{
  "stem": "17526.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Later on when we got up, we could see the chunk that that bomb that dug into this camp.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We survived it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Life in the camp was horrible.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was awful.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But somehow we survived until January the 18th, 1945.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "All at once, orders came, we are evacuated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We are put down in columns and we started marching.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We left about 2,000 strong.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "I think half of us got lost on the way.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "What happened was we froze, most of them froze.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "At night, we were pushed down into what do you call-- barns.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It-- it was all farmland that we walked through.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And wherever you went through a farm, naturally we raided the farms and all of the-- I remember one time I got a hold of-- of potato peels and this was like-- like manna from heaven.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And we got-- gobbled up all the garbage that we could raid on the way.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But when we were pushed in through these farms, that's when we raided the farms.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "The next day, they would come and round us up to march and people with hide in stacks of hay or in these-- in these fields.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they will go with the bayonets and just make sure that everybody-- my uncle, my father's brother, I saw him a day before, the next day I didn't see him.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Don't forget, the columns were hundreds-- hundreds of us going.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "So it was like for a stretch of a half a mile.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "Now, the German guards were on both sides, and if you fell on the snow or you couldn't walk anymore, they put you on a wagon at the very tail of the column and later on they shot them.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "One time I tried to pull a quickie.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
